title: EastEnders spoiler: Heartbroken Lee Carter set to murder father Mick over Whitney kiss?
text:

EastEnders fans may soon be saying their final goodbyes to Mick Carter. 
Following the jaw-dropping bus crash, his unconscious daughter-in-law Whitney was rushed to hospital while her husband Lee was nowhere to be seen. 
When she eventually came round, the Queen Vic landlord was lovingly right by her side and the pair kissed. Although he eventually pulled away, this is the second time she's cheated with her hubby's dad. 
Now, it's just a matter of time before Lee finds out the truth and when he does, Mick could be in grave danger, warns actor Danny-Boy Hatchard. Will Lee kill father Mick? (Photo: BBC) 
"It's hard to say which direction Lee would go in, but he'd be left feeling worthless," he told the Daily Star. "I think he could lash out and hit Mick, or just fall apart. This is the second time it's happened, after all. Read More EastEnders spoiler: Ian Beale to be diagnosed with prostate cancer after frequent toilet trips? 
"My own instincts tell me he'd go into self-destruct mode. Of course he'd be broken-hearted, that goes without saying - so something has to give." Lee is set to find out that his wife Whitney cheated with his dad for the second time (Photo: BBC) 
We're not sure exactly what Danny-Boy is hinting at, but given Lee's current state, nothing would surprise us. 
The actor's words come after his Wikipedia page was recently hacked with claims that his character leaves the soap after murdering his father. Read More 
It read: "He was axed in August 2016, and will leave the soap in 2017 after killing his father Mick Carter. Mick's tragic (and rather surprising end) will happen in "a dramatic fight outside the Archers over [Lee's] debt." Danny-Boy's Wikipedia page was hacked a few weeks ago 
While we're not sure whether we buy that EastEnders bosses would kill off our beloved Mick, one thing we do know for sure is that Lee's days in Walford are numbered. 
Mirror Online has contacted EastEnders for comment.
